        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Automated</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">One or more active RemoteSiteSetting records have URLs starting with http://. Apex callouts to these endpoints transmit all request and response data unencrypted.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Impact__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Any network observer between Salesforce data centers and the HTTP endpoint can read the full callout payload in plaintext, including any credentials, tokens, or sensitive business data transmitted.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Replace all http:// Remote Site Setting URLs with https:// equivalents. Update the corresponding callout code to use the HTTPS URLs.</value>
    </values>
